Per Order of the Presiding Judge, Felony Division, the defendant's request filed 2/23/15 is hereby assigned to the Hon. Ellen R. Brostrom, Br. 6, for review. mag
Defendant called the postconviction department and asked that her request to terminate probation filed on 2/23/15 be referred to a judge for review.
Letter in response to defendant's request to terminate probation.
Defendant's pro se request to terminate probation.

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher Lee Hartley.  David A. Feiss appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.  

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.
On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Present/Cause Fraudulent Insurance Claim, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.395(1)(a), a class A misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

Statements made as to sentencing. 
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Huber privileges for work.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
* Obtain and maintain employment and/or school and/or vocational training.
* Restitution payable to William B. of PMA Companies for $33,856.24 at a rate of $200.00 monthly, commencing 11/1/2014 and the 1st of each month until end of probation then remaining balance to convert to a civil judgment with tax intercept .  Bail to be applied if applicable.  Payable first during probation.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered.

  Filed,

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher Lee Hartley.  David A. Feiss appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.  Court vacated the stayed warrant. Defendant missed court due to work conflict.  Defendant to pay the remaining balance of restitution.

Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley in court via telephone.  Brad A. Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.   Defendant is in compliance with the agreement.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until next court date.  Calendar call scheduled for September 8, 2014 at 03:00 pm.  Review hearing scheduled for October 7, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher L Hartley.  David A Feiss appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Parties advised the Court that they have reached a Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement, received by the Court, signed by all parties and filed.  

Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Plea Questionaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The Court reviewed and approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the proceedings suspended for a period of six months.  Court ordered all terms and conditions of bail to continue and ordered case continued before Branch 06 for review.


  Review hearing scheduled for August 25, 2014 at 08:30 am.
File retained in court.

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher L Hartley.  David A Feiss appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Final pretrial held.  Parties advise the Court that this case will be reserved for deferred prosecution agreement.  Court ordered all terms and conditions of bail to continue and ordered the 6/23/14 trial date be vacated.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for June 23, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher Lee Hartley.  David A. Feiss appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel requested a trial date.  Court set the following motion schedule: movant must file on or before 4/28/14; response due by 5/19/14; reply (if any) due by 5/27/14.  All motions in limine, jury instructions and witness lists are to be filed one week prior to the final pretrial date.  Court ordered all terms and conditions of bail to continue.  Final pre-trial scheduled for June 16, 2014 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for June 23, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher Hartley.  Kimberly D. Schoepp appeared on behalf of David A. Feiss for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  rn  At defense counsel's request, this case was added to the calendar on today's date, as defense counsel just received a volumnious amount of discovery and requested a later date instead of the original 3/03/14.  ADA Feiss, Attorney Hartley and this clerk selected a new date.  Court ordered case adjourned before Branch 20 and that all terms and conditions of bail remain.  Scheduling conference scheduled for April 7, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Destiny Carter in court with attorney Christopher Hartley.  David A Feiss appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:Scott Lafleur-Milwaukee County District Attorney's Office Investigator.  Exhibits 1, 2 and 3 have been marked, offered and received into evidence.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 20.  Exhibits are ordered withdrawn.  Scheduling conference scheduled for March 3, 2014 at 08:30 am.
